[144.128, "o", "\u001b[2;2H├── test-r                                        \u001b[3;2H│   ├── re-exports macros from test-r-macro      \u001b[4;2H│   ├── re-exports runtime pieces from test-r-core              \u001b[5;2H│   └── core module     # registration API bridging macros to core runtime\u001b[6;2H│                                                                                                 \u001b[7;2H├── cargo-test-r                                                                 \u001b[8;2H│   └── CLI tool for running test-r via Cargo workflows                         \u001b[9;2H│                                                                                                                            \u001b[10;2H├── test-r-github                                                                \u001b[11;2H│   └── generates GitHub Actions workflow files       \u001b[12;2H│                                                 \u001b[13;2H├── test-r-example                                                      "]
[144.129, "o", "                                        \u001b[14;2H│   └── example project using test-r without tokio                               \u001b[15;2H│                                                                      \u001b[16;2H└── test-r-example-tokio                       \u001b[17;2H    └── example project using test-r with tokio                       \u001b[18;2H```                                            \u001b[19;2H                                                                                   \u001b[20;2HAnd here is the dependency relationship between\u001b[20;50Hthe\u001b[20;54Hcrates:\u001b[21;2H                                                                              \u001b[22;2H```text                                         \u001b[23;2H              ┌──────────────┐                                                      \u001b[24;2H              │  test-r-core │                  \u001b[25;2H              └──────┬───────┘                                                  "]
[144.129, "o", "     \u001b[26;2H                     │                          \u001b[27;2H          ┌──────────┴──────────┐                                              \u001b[28;2H          │                     │               \u001b[29;2H┌─────────▼─────────┐   ┌───────▼───────┐                                                                                                                                  \u001b[30;2H│   test-r-macro    │   │    test-r     │                                        \u001b[31;2H│ (proc macros)     │   │ public facade │                                          \u001b[32;2H└─────────┬─────────┘   └───────┬───────┘       \u001b[33;2H          │                     │                                             \u001b[34;2H          └──────────┬──────────┘              \u001b["]
[144.129, "o", "35;2H                     │                                                              \u001b[36;2H        ┌────────────▼────────────┐            \u001b[37;2H        │ example / example-tokio │                                                 \u001b[38;2H        └─────────────────────────┘            \u001b[39;2H                                                                              \u001b[40;2HOther workspace tools:                         \u001b[41;2H- cargo-test-r     (standalone cargo extension)                                \u001b[42;2H- test-r-github    (standalone workflow generator)\u001b[43;2H```                                                                                  \u001b[44;2H                                               \u001b[45;2HIf you want, I can also draw this as:                                                                                                                                      \u001b[46;2H         "]
